R is an open-source statistical package that is widely used in academia, research and industry. R Studio provides a nice interface for R and provides some very useful functionality.

**You will be coding in R/R Studio and interpreting R code and output in this course. So, the purpose of the learnR Modules you will be working with this term is to give you experience with R code that may come in handy as you are working with data.** We will be using the University of Toronto JupyterHub to access the R/R Studio environment. To access R Studio on JupyterHub, use your UTORid and password to login at [https://r.datatools.utoronto.ca/](https://r.datatools.utoronto.ca/). Alternatively, if you wish to install R (and RStudio) on your own machine, R is freely available for download at [http://cran.r-project.org/](http://cran.r-project.org) for Windows, MacOS, and Linux operating systems and RStudio is available at [https://posit.co/downloads/](https://posit.co/downloads/).

This activity can be done in your browser, as you go through each of the chunks. You do not need to download R/R Studio or use JupyterHub for this activity.

In this module we will be going over:

-   creating objects & variables in R
-   how to use and write functions
-   vectors & data types
-   how to deal with missing data
-   how to create a for loop
-   exploring data frames
